  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing App Aesthetics**\n\nOkay, I\'m examining the visual elements. It\'s becoming clear this app, Ember, will be dark with amber highlights. My focus is now on replicating the provided screenshots and understanding how those elements will integrate. I need to nail down the specific UI components.\n\n\n**Defining Home Screen Layout**\n\nI\'ve moved on to the Home screen, working out its components. I see a clear header with \"EMBER\" and those key icons. The \"Welcome Back\" section feels intuitive, followed by quick actions and a prominent announcement. I\'m focusing on the upcoming events card design, including the custom image and \"Register Now\" button, as well as the bento-style stats grid. Finally, I\'m defining the bottom navigation bar.\n\n\n**Detailing Form Components**\n\nI\'m now diving into the specifics of the form card. I\'ve broken down the segmented control for \"Devotional vs Testimony,\" and the input fields for title and message. The warning banner and \"Submit for Review\" button are designed. I\'m taking the \"EMBER PORTAL V2.4.0\" note into account, too. Bottom navigation is set.\n\n\n**Constructing User Profile**\n\nI\'m now building the user profile page. I see the \"PROFILE\" header with a settings icon, then the avatar with its glow and status indicator. User information comes next, followed by stats in a Bento grid. I\'m focusing now on the menu items and ensuring each leads to the intended section. I\'m also confirming the proper bottom navigation placement.\n\n\n**Evaluating Data Persistence**\n\nOkay, I\'m assessing data persistence. While I initially considered Firebase, the instructions don\'t explicitly require it. I\'m leaning toward local storage persistence. I think local state/localStorage gives me the most flexibility for now. I\'m confident I can build a robust React-driven applet with localStorage for persistence.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Local State**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on data persistence. Local state with localStorage feels like the optimal, friction-free starting point, and it ensures instant performance. I need to make sure this meets the minimal requirements. I\'m exploring the `metadata.json` file now and considering what skills are actually applicable. It seems like standard React with localStorage will be perfect for this!\n\n\n**Incorporating Image Assets**\n\nI\'m now integrating the image URLs. I see the provided HTML gives us several options for Aaron\'s profile picture. My focus is on determining how these images will be used within the user profile page. I am selecting the primary image source for display, ensuring optimal resolution and performance.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 10
      nanos: 624764858
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
