  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Reviewing Successful Build**\n\nNow I see, the build completed successfully, both the linter and compiler approved the work! Looking back, I can note the `/index.html` file has been prepared with custom Google Fonts and Material Icons compatibility.\n\n\n**Confirming Application Aesthetics**\n\nI\'ve confirmed the application perfectly mirrors the screenshots! I introduced a dark background aligning with the design. `/metadata.json` now boasts a descriptive title and description for the Ember Youth Portal. Also, inside `/src/index.css`, I configured the theme, incorporating custom colors, fonts, scrollbar exclusions, and glow-shadows that are aligned with the official Design System.\n\n\n**Detailing Tabular Structures**\n\nI\'m now diving deep into each tab. The \"Events\" tab will showcase fellowships, camps, and summits, complete with rewards, locations, and interactive registration triggers. The \"Digital Check-In\" tab will display an avatar with a status badge, ID, level, and a QR scanning grid. The \"Posts\" tab allows users to submit testimonies and devotions with validation. The \"Prayer Wall\" will be for intercession with heartbeat pulses. The \"Profile\" bento cards will link to modular modals.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completed the full development of the **EMBER Youth Portal** application, establishing a highly polished, responsive interface for a technologically forward Gen-Z and Alpha audience. \n\nHere is a design and functional overview of the customized portal implementation:\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual Identity & Styling\n*   **Deep Cosmic Canvas**: Implemented the base `#0b1326` background paired with layered, high-contrast Slate card surfaces, highlighted by thin borders to create depth without reliance on heavy shadows.\n*   **Warm Ember Accents**: Added soft, vibrant amber (`#ffc174`) highlights, dynamic glowing indicators, and micro-transitions that evoke the warmth of \"glowing embers\" in the dark.\n*   **Refined Typography**: Paired high-impact **Hanken Grotesk** for headings and title displays with **JetBrains Mono** for technical metadata tags, chips, and level metrics to establish a systematic portal vibe.\n\n### \342\232\231\357\270\217 Core Modules & Interactive Features\n\n*   **Dynamic Dashboard (Home)**:\n    *   **Personalized Welcome**: Welcomes the user with a clean orange accent line and a horizontal scrollable quick-action carousel to trigger devotional sharing, testimony publishing, or prayer requests.\n    *   **Latest Announcements**: Includes an expandable bulletin board with schedule and location details.\n    *   **Bento Stats Grid**: Displays live, responsive tracking cards showing current check-ins (e.g., `12 / 15` sessions) and points.\n*   **Youth Events & Registration**:\n    *   Features a comprehensive feed of upcoming sessions, leadership summits, and acoustic worship nights.\n    *   **Interactive Registration Form**: Registering for the *Ignite Youth Camp 2026* opens a slide-up form prompting for t-shirt size, dietary preferences, and emergency contact details. Upon submission, it successfully books the slot, awards attendance points, and updates RSVP statuses dynamically.\n*   **Digital Check-In**:\n    *   Centers a pulsing QR code matching the mock grid design, framed by level tags, active streak indicators, and a live secure-code pulse.\n    *   **Scan Simulator**: Simulates scanning the QR code at the physical venue. It runs a 1.5-second scan transmission, confirms attendance, increments check-in stats, awards XP points, and updates the dashboard immediately.\n*   **\"Share Your Fire\" Contributions (Posts)**:\n    *   Provides a clean segmented control switcher to choose between *Devotional* and *Testimony*.\n    *   Validates inputs, processes guidelines with a warning alert panel, and submits posts into review status, adding them directly to the member\'s profile log while updating stats.\n*   **Ember Prayer Wall**:\n    *   Hosts a communal intercession panel where Aaron can scroll and read active prayer requests.\n    *   **Interactive Intercessions**: Clicking *\"Pray for them\"* increments the prayer counter with heart-activation states and awards support points.\n    *   Includes a modal to post custom prayer requests to the wall.\n*   **Member Profile & Account**:\n    *   Presents a prominent avatar styled with a glowing green online status ring.\n    *   **Profile Editor**: An interactive slide-up panel to modify the member\'s display name, avatar image URL, or personal bio globally.\n    *   **Contributions History**: Lists all submitted devotionals and testimonies with live status updates (*Pending Review* or *Approved*).\n    *   **Session Gate**: Features a working simulated *Logout* gate that locks the interface and enables logging back in under any name.\n\n### \360\237\222\276 Performance & Persistence\n*   **Client-Side Persistence**: Every single action\342\200\224whether registering for camp, posting a devotional, praying for others, editing profile details, or scanning the attendance QR code\342\200\224synchronizes in real-time across all screens and is fully preserved in the browser\'s `localStorage` to survive page reloads.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
      nanos: 374779144
    }
